-- Hong Kong's main share index lifted by Tencent's jump
-- By Grace Li
-- Thu May 15, 2014 04:07AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 15 (Reuters) - Hong Kong's main index rose to its highest close in nearly a month, lifted by tech heavyweight Tencent Holdings Ltd., which posted better-than-expected results and announced a share-split.

The Hang Seng Index ended up 0.7 percent at 22,730.86 points, its highest close since April 17. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong was down 0.2 percent. Mainland indexes both fell more than 1 percent on Thursday. Tencent <2988.HK> jumped 5.8 percent on its first quarter results and news it would conduct a five-for-one share split to attract small investors.